<br>Spellmaking, I know it's not a actual skill, but it's still cool as hell. All I have made so far is a waterbreathing spell with MUCH longer duration. Once my skills hit 100 I will start to invent some really nasty effects. Have you made any cool spells yet?<br><br>And finally, enchantment.<br>Well, what can I say?<br>ROXOR!!!!<br>So far I don't have very much skill in it, but once I do...<br><br>For those who havn't peeked at it, you pick what effects you want the item to have and what the durations, type of activation and target area should be. So the number of possible items you can design is virtually unlimited.<br><br>Gaad, the tradeskills in EverQuest should have been something like this. Nowadays they are at least useful, but they are still totally static. Farm item A, B, C and D, and combine them to create item E. Bleah!<br><br>With Morrowind enchantment, you loot a great item somewhere. Then you go and fight one of the local ubermobs and trap it's soul in a soulgem. And then you start playing around with the skill. Well, &quot;great item and ubermob&quot; if you want to make a really good item. The better item and the stronger soul, the more enchantment points you get. This make the item harder to make, but it also give room for much more powerful effects.  <p>Love, Edeina<br>Highelf Arch Mage of Erollisi.<br>Citizen of <a href="http://pub42.ezboard.com/bayonaero">Ayonae Ro</a>, member of <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/beternalwrath">Eternal Wrath</a>.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uhalochanter.showPublicProfile?language=EN>HaloChanter</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bored at work? Yeah... that's it</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/15/02 2:15:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tradeskills in Morrowind - enchantment in particular</span><hr size=1> My enchantment skill is pathetic to say the least. So I paid a mage to do it <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>My first ever one was a ring with healing 2 - 10 points on! I had no friggin idea what i was doing. Kinda getting the hang of it now. <br>I agree, the tradeskill system seems extremely deep. You could make a serious living from it, unlike EverQuest.<br>Only thing is, when you start to create uber_item_01, none of the fucking vendors can afford to buy it.<br>That's the ONE thing I hate about Morrowind, barely any of the merchants have more than 2k on them to buy your stuff! <p>Haloface 57th Beguiler<br>Gegweiani 59th Preserver<br>Nusajaa 54th Elementalist<br>Sspeed 45th Monk<br>Dakok 20th Warrior<br>Proud Nipple of Legend of the Jokers.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uander00.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ander00</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/17/02 3:02:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.gerti.at/richi/photo020402.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tradeskills in Morrowind - enchantment in particular</span><hr size=1> enchanting things can be quite cool, especially since it provides a way of making all those expensive items into nifty little effects since enchanters buy most types of items. after enchanting you can turn some of your treasures into cash and proceed with the next item to enchant. i think i've done it a little bit on the powergaming side though, now constantly regenerating 12 hitpoints per second amongst other effects. i just wish i wouldn't always do silly things like killing the enchanters and hitting quicksave right afterwards though <!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.gerti.at/richi/an06.gif"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END-->.<br><br>if you don't have the ammounts of cash needed for regeneration items and the likes you might want to start with an effective levitation-item and an item or two that heal you when used, those really make life in morrowind a lot easier, in particular if you aren't much of a spellcaster.<br><br>by the way, it's often a good idea to bribe the traders you're exchanging lots of gold with to get better prices from them and if you have trouble selling some phat loot you can trade it for whatever gold a vendor has and a whole lot of valuable light-weight items like gems and scrolls (provided he/she has some to sell of course) which you can then distribute to various other vendors.<br><br><br>cheers <!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.gerti.at/richi/an18.gif"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--> <p><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=5399"><img src="http://www.gerti.at/richi/sig020402.jpg" border="0"></a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uazndailow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>AznDailow</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Boardfellow</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/17/02 5:20:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re:</span><hr size=1> Enchanting is definately cool. I remember being a tad ticked when I found a couple of artifacts from previous Elder Scrolls games, and they didn't have any special abilities on them. I was like &quot;WTF!! Gyp!&quot;, and then I remember enchantment.<br><br>Some artifacts (like Volundrung, or Auriel's Shield/Bow) don't have special abilities, but they do have a TON of enchantment points available for them. I haven't checked myself, but I think Volundrung has ~100 points available, whereas other normal weapons have a lot less. I think my Daedric Katana only had 24 points, and an Exquisite Robe had 40.<br><br>The skill itself really does give you an idea of just how powerful some of the items in the game are, however. If you look at the Robe of St. Rorlis (with constant  15 points of regen for health/fatigue), and try to duplicate it at your local enchanter, you'll see that it requires a LOT of points, something in the neighbourhood of 400. Not just any normal robe will do to make that powerful of an enchantment to say the least <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uedeina.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Edeina</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Board Mistress</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/17/02 6:46:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.one.se/users/chribesk/edeina.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re:</span><hr size=1> I gave up for now trying to make my own permanent levitate helm. Had a NPC make it for me, costed 46k. Never intended to save the game afterwards, but it crashed anyway when I tried to &quot;zone&quot; while wearing the helmet. <br><br>So next time I will save the game anyway, just to see if it was